article.headline: Mazzante's season-high 38 powers Nittany Lions
article.linkText: Mazzante scores 38 to lead Penn St. past Old Dominion
article.story:
STATE COLLEGE, Pa. (AP) -- Kelly Mazzante scored a season-high 38
points as Penn State (No. 15 ESPN/USA Today, No. 13 AP) beat Old Dominion 81-74 Tuesday night.

	   Tanisha Wright added 16 points and Jess Brungo 12 for Penn State
(15-4), which led by 21 with 15:42 left and withstood a 25-9 Old
Dominion run to hold on.

	   Kim Giddens had a season-high 28 points to lead the Lady
Monarchs (8-6), who were 17-for-22 from the floor in the second
half and shot nearly 61 percent for the game.

	   Giddens, who came in averaging 5.9 points per game, hit a layup
with 15:16 remaining and scored 10 points during the run that
brought Old Dominion to 69-64 with 7:17 left. But the Lady Monarchs
were unable to close the gap any further.

	   Shareese Grant scored 14 points for Old Dominion, while Okeisha
Howard added 11 and Max Nhassengo 10.

	   Mazzante scored 26 points in the first half of her 20th career
30-point game, and finished with her highest total of the season.
She was 12-for-12 from the free-throw line, one shy of the school's
single-game record.

	   With 9:22 left in the first half and the score tied at 20, the
Lady Lions went on an 18-4 run behind 13 points from Mazzante. They
stretched the advantage to 52-35 by halftime.
